technologyData.name: Node.js
technologyData.description: Node.js is an open-source, cross-platform, JavaScript runtime environment that executes JavaScript code outside a web browser.

technologyData.name: Brightcove
technologyData.description: Brightcove is a cloud-based online video platform.

technologyData.name: React
technologyData.description: React is an open-source JavaScript library for building user interfaces or UI components.

technologyData.name: Emotion
technologyData.description: Emotion is a library designed for writing CSS styles with JavaScript.

technologyData.name: Nginx
technologyData.description: Nginx is a web server that can also be used as a reverse proxy, load balancer, mail proxy and HTTP cache.

technologyData.name: Express
technologyData.description: Express is a web application framework for Node.js, released as free and open-source software under the MIT License. It is designed for building web applications and APIs.

technologyData.name: OneTrust
technologyData.description: OneTrust is a cloud-based data privacy management compliance platform.

technologyData.name: Google Tag Manager
technologyData.description: Google Tag Manager is a tag management system (TMS) that allows you to quickly and easily update measurement codes and related code fragments collectively known as tags on your website or mobile app.

technologyData.name: Amplitude
technologyData.description: Amplitude is a web and mobile analytics solution with cross-platform user journey tracking, user behavior analysis and segmentation capabilities.

technologyData.name: reCAPTCHA
technologyData.description: reCAPTCHA is a free service from Google that helps protect websites from spam and abuse.

technologyData.name: Google Analytics
technologyData.description: Google Analytics is a free web analytics service that tracks and reports website traffic.

technologyData.name: Priority Hints
technologyData.description: Priority Hints exposes a mechanism for developers to signal a relative priority for browsers to consider when fetching resources.

technologyData.name: Loadable-Components
technologyData.description: Loadable-Components is a library to solve the React code-splitting client-side and server-side.

technologyData.name: web-vitals
technologyData.description: The web-vitals JavaScript is a tiny, modular library for measuring all the web vitals metrics on real users.

technologyData.name: HSTS
technologyData.description: HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) informs browsers that the site should only be accessed using HTTPS.

technologyData.name: RSS
technologyData.description: RSS is a family of web feed formats used to publish frequently updated works—such as blog entries, news headlines, audio, and video—in a standardized format.

technologyData.name: Open Graph
technologyData.description: Open Graph is a protocol that is used to integrate any web page into the social graph.
